    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1921-05-19T09:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1921-05-19T09:00:00-05:00" n="754"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d754">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">361.11/3729: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Norway</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Schmedeman</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Christiania</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-05-19T15:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 19, 1921—3 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received 3:49 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>21. Dr. Nansen has received the following from Moscow.</p>
                <quote rend="blockquote">
                    <p>“May 15th. Answering your wireless message of May 13th are [we] to understand
                        that the detention of American citizens in Russia is the only hindrance to
                        the resumption of trade and <hi rend="italic">de facto</hi> relations
                        between Russia and the United States of America.”</p>
                </quote>
                <p>He wishes to reply personally and not on behalf of the Government of the United
                    States that such detention is not the only hindrance but is a very serious one
                    and that he fears if continued it will make the situation much worse. Before
                    sending this he wishes assurances of your approval but believes his reply should
                    be sent at the earliest possible moment.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Schmedeman</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
